== Python Server ==

Tiny server for python script execution.

== Overview ==

After building program using GNU Make utility, two files are created:
1. PythonServer - python script execution server.
2. PythonSender - program for sending python files to PythonServer for execution.

== Usage example ==

1. Start python server in shell:
	cd ~/PythonServer
	./PythonServer --num_thread 5

   or start python server as a daemon:
	./PythonServer --num_thread 5 --d

   and stop PythonServer daemon:
	./PythonServer --stop

2. Send python script from file "example.py":
	cd ~/PythonServer
	./PythonSender localhost 5555 example.py


Shell command for getting additional information about command line parameters:
	./PythonServer --help
